      "id": 324291,
      "is_internal": false,
      "editable": false,
      "type": "Activities::BugResolved",
      "message": "Thanks for the patience @atom!\n\nThe resolution here took a bit longer because the \"fix\" was a change in a manual process. We intentionally used lightweight validation process when our stricter validation was not possible (primarily: for properties without published SPF/DKIM records), and this process was based largely on a subjective judgement call on the risk of a mistake. The same technique was not repeatable for most sites on the internet, which is why it failed to reproduce consistently.\n\nIt is clear that having an error-prone judgement call as part of this process was a mistake. We've updated our team's process to avoid this scenario in the future. Thanks for pointing out our mistake.",
      "automated_response": false,
